<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A mother has drowned in rough surf while swimming with her daughter in Queensland.</p>

<p>The 34-year-old was pulled from the water by surfers at First Bay in Coolum Beach on the Sunshine Coast just after 7 on Monday morning.</p>

<p>The woman's rescuers did CPR on her on the beach before emergency services including paramedics arrived.</p>

<p>Paramedics took over, but unfortunately the woman was pronounced dead at the scene.</p>

<p>A 34-year-old mother has drowned after going for a swim with her daughter at Coolum Beach (pictured) on Queensland's Sunshine Coast</p>

<p>The Courier Mail reported the mother is from Toowoomba and was holidaying in the area with her extended family.</p>

<p>Police Sergeant Peter Blake described the death as 'tragic'.</p>

<p>A Queensland police spokesperson told Daily Mail Australia they were not treating the death as suspicious.</p>

<p>A report will be prepared for the coroner.Â </p>

<p>The mother and her daughter were swimming in rough conditions at First Bay (pictured) before she was pulled from the water by surfers</p>
